			  	Thank you for your kind words =). This has not been an easy path for any of us, players, devs, it doesn't matter. But the era of the bugs has been long in archspace from the very beginning to today. Apache errors still reign supreme in the minds and hatred of many vets. TheDAZ leaving was a sad day for Archspace, our future was unsure. Buzzrock, although he and I did not see eye to eye, he did his damndest for us and even he too folded. Now however, we have a dedicated development team who will make sure your game is enjoyable and *hopefully* crashfree. I have spent the last week trying to crash the dev server, not easy anymore. The game is also much more balanced now, things are usable, things will not absolutely decimate everything else. With this new era comes a new class of players...<br />
<br />
-DarkElf/Seiffer<br />
-Balance Dev			   <P align=right></P>
